reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 6, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Slice & Dice for a reasonable price!
reviews.reviewText: I was new to buying specialty knives for the kitchen, and this was a impulse buy also get with a veggie one. I have not had a more productive 2 weeks in the kitchen. This knife has been a joy to use, for someone who didn’t know he needed these, I can’t look back.The knife is heavy and solid, but is extremely well balanced, making handling this EXTREMELY sharp knife a breeze. I was unsure about the black finish, but have had no issue with it, and absolutely find it helpful while using. The stark contrast helps me eye my cuts as well. 2 weeks in and not a single issue with the quality of the item.I recommend this for anyone looking to expand their culinary learning, or just moving up from a $60 full set.Only issue...I ordered the black finish (also the vegetable blade and two others) and I did not get the plastic sheath to store it. I am scared the edge or finish may be damaged. 😞

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 11, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars A good-lookin' knife.
reviews.reviewText: I bought this on sale for about 2/3 the normal price. I was a little disappointed that no sheath is included but not a deal-breaker. It does come with a little sharpener, which I've never used. I've so far only used a steel on it and it's held up well. I use this as a sort of utility knife or the knife that leaves the kitchen (outside bbq stuff, for instance); just sort of the bang-around knife. The coat is still holding strong and it's honestly still performing well (6 months later). I don't like the western handle much, but that's a preference for me.I'm not sure how it will hold up under a whet stone yet - the coating may be compromised. I would say if you're looking to replace your every day knife and can get this one at a good price (I'd say 1/2 or less) AND want that unique look then I would recommend it. If you're looking for something more long-term then it may be better to look elsewhere; especially is aesthetics aren't a priority.
